# StartOS Actions

Follow sibling actions (`lnSettings.ts`, `mostroSettings.ts`, `expirationSettings.ts`) before inventing new patterns.

## Structure

```typescript
export const inputSpec = InputSpec.of({ /* Value.number | Value.text | Value.select */ })

export const mySettings = sdk.Action.withInput(
  'my-settings',
  async () => ({
    name: i18n('...'),
    description: i18n('...'),
    warning: null,
    allowedStatuses: 'any',
    group: i18n('Mostro'),
    visibility: 'enabled',
  }),
  inputSpec,
  async ({ effects }) => { /* prefill from daemon_settings.read(...).once() */ },
  async ({ effects, input }) => { /* save via daemon_settings.merge */ },
)
```

## Save handler

- Use `daemon_settings.merge(effects, { section: { ... } })` — partial updates only
- Arrays in TOML → comma-separated text in UI; parse on save (see `nostrSettings.ts`, `mostroSettings.ts`)
- Empty text for optional arrays → `[]` (accept all)
- Register new actions in `actions/index.ts`

## Imports

Keep at top of file: `storeJson`, `daemon_settings`, `i18n`, `sdk`. No inline imports.
